items.caption: As much as it pained you to see summer fade, there's no denying the excitement that starts to bubble for fall coziness and [all pumpkin everything](http://www.teenvogue.com/gallery/12-pumpkin-spice-treats-fall). But (perhaps) the best part of the new season? All the amazing new beauty products you get to try out and debut  — even better, you can do so on a budget with these drugstore diamonds. Click through and stock up.

items.title: [Maybelline The Colossal Chaotic Lash](http://www.drugstore.com/products/prod.asp?pid=558375&catid=183542&aid=338666&aparam=558375&kpid=558375&CAWELAID=120142990000122585&CAGPSPN=pla&kpid=558375)
items.caption: Go bold or go home. Add some rockstar flair to your lashes with this amped up formula.
Lazy girls, rejoice! The ultimate one-step cleanser, Neutrogena's lightweight cleansing oil acts like a magnet to remove all traces of dirt, excess oil, and makeup trapped within your pores.

items.title: [Suave Moroccan Infusion Styling Oil](http://www.drugstore.com/products/prod.asp?pid=461373&catid=337239&aid=338666&aparam=461373&kpid=461373&CAWELAID=120142990000002009&CAGPSPN=pla&kpid=461373)
items.caption: It was hard to imagine a styling oil that didn't weigh down strands before we stumbled upon Suave's Moroccan Infusion Styling Oil. Infused with authentic Moroccan argan oil, this lightweight formula conditions and adds an insane amount of shine.
Contouring can be complicated. Instead, stick with strobing. This shimmery highlighter will give you instant cheekbones. Perfect for nailing your school pic.

items.title: [Biore Pore Penetrating Charcoal Bar](http://www.ulta.com/ulta/browse/productDetail.jsp?productId=xlsImpprod12001091)
items.caption: Vacuum out clogged pores with a penetrating charcoal bar, designed to draw out deep-seated dirt and oil. A hint of natural peppermint oil leaves skin with a tingling sensation, so your face will feel extra refreshed.

items.title: [Milani Fierce Foil Eyeliner](http://www.drugstore.com/products/prod.asp?pid=547958&catid=183537&cmbProdBrandFilter=55311&aid=338666&aparam=547958&kpid=547958&CAWELAID=120142990000116546&CAGPSPN=pla&kpid=547958)
items.caption: Accessorize your lids with these epic foil liners. They're basically jewelry for your eyes.

items.title: [Benzac Acne Eliminating Cleanser](http://www.drugstore.com/products/prod.asp?pid=558439&catid=338324&aid=338666&aparam=558439&kpid=558439&CAWELAID=120142990000122921&CAGPSPN=pla&kpid=558439)
items.caption: Frustrated by your past failed attempts at clearing acne? Try switching to a cleanser containing benzoyl peroxide to wipe out breakout-inducing bacteria once and for all, like Benzac Acne Eliminating Cleanser.

items.title: [Dove Oxygen Moisture Conditioner](http://www.target.com/p/dove-oxygen-moisture-conditioner-12-oz/-/A-15023622)
items.caption: Do you often find your strands falling flat by first period? Get the bounce and volume you've always wanted — and make it last all day long — with an oxygen-infused conditioner like Dove Oxygen Moisture Conditioner.

items.title: [Carol's Daughter Monoi Repairing Anti-Breakage Spray](http://www.ulta.com/ulta/browse/productDetail.jsp?productId=xlsImpprod5430057)
items.caption: End excessive shedding, and stop split ends before they have a chance to start with a fortifying leave-in conditioner. We love Carol's Daughter Monoi Repairing Anti-Breakage Spray, which is packed with the vitamins and minerals necessary to revive sagging strands after one too many passes of a flatiron.

items.title: [EcoTools Lovely Looks Set](http://www.walgreens.com/store/c/ecotools-lovely-looks-set/ID=prod6210709-product?ext=gooBeauty_PLA_Face_Brushes_prod6210709_pla&adtype=pla&kpid=sku6184445&sst=9050e5d9-6275-44e5-9a2b-146de0ccc510&kpid=sku6184445)
items.caption: The perfect makeup moment starts with the right tools. These adorable brushes get the job done in a flash.

items.title: [Sally Hansen Luxe Lace Nail Polish](http://www.drugstore.com/sally-hansen-luxe-lace-nail-color-crochet/qxp547475?catid=196092)
items.caption: Once school starts, you really won't have time to sit at home and paint intricate nail art, like you did during the summer. Instead, opt for this party-in-a-bottle. It leaves a fabric feel in just two coats.

items.title: [Cera Ve Renewing SA Cleanser](http://www.drugstore.com/cerave-renewing-sa-cleanser/qxp547768)
items.caption: Start fresh with an exfoliating cleanser that removes dead skin cells sans harsh grains or beads. We recommend CeraVe's Renewing SA Cleanser, which exfoliates and leaves skin extra soft and super smooth.

items.title: [Sexy Hair Big Sexy Hair Push Up Thickening Finishing Spray](http://www.ulta.com/ulta/browse/productDetail.jsp?productId=xlsImpprod12901001&skuId=2290409&cmpid=PS_Non!google!Product_Listing_Ads&cagpspn=pla&CAWELAID=330000200000344028&catargetid=330000200000332392&cadevice=c&gclid=Cj0KEQjwmNuuBRDTu5rDjr2kxJsBEiQAWlm6UvgDmWQu0SYrWOwe97WnNkcXUoX-Zk47Lr1Rz7oSTy4aAgJB8P8HAQ)
items.caption: Conquer your fear of finishing sprays (ugh, the stiffness!) with a crunch-free formula that also amps up volume, like Sexy Hair Big Sexy Hair Push Up Thickening Finishing Spray.

items.title: [Flower Hollywood Secret Concealer Kit](http://www.walmart.com/ip/FLOWER-CONCEALER-KIT-HOLLYWOOD-SECRET-0.04-OZ/42683491)
items.caption: Mix and match the colors in this quad to banish redness, cover breakouts, and mask under-eye circles. It's basically your post-all-nighter BFF.
Smoky eyes made easy! If larger-than-life shadow palettes overwhelm you, you're in luck. This three-shade approach makes blending and shading as easy as, well, 1, 2, 3.

items.title: [Olay Foaming Face Wash For Sensitive Skin](http://www.drugstore.com/products/prod.asp?pid=330846&catid=182285&aid=338666&aparam=330846&kpid=330846&CAWELAID=120142990000036014&CAGPSPN=pla&kpid=330846)
items.caption: Gentlest. Cleanser. Ever. 100% soap-free, oil-free, and fragrance-free, Olay's Foaming Face Wash lathers to a rich, creamy foam that's soft, yet effective enough to treat the most sensitive skin.

items.title: [SheaMoisture Fruit Fusion Coconut Water Weightless Hair Mask](http://www.ulta.com/ulta/browse/productDetail.jsp?productId=xlsImpprod12731005)
items.caption: Tired of your hair looking lifeless, no matter what hydrating mask you slather on each week? Try a frizz-fighting formula to smooth and soothe thirsty strands, like SheaMoisture Fruit Fusion Coconut Water Weightless Hair Mask.
Selfie skin, right this way. Apply this mattifying formula and watch as your skin becomes #nofilter fabulous.

items.title: [E.l.f. Studio Need It Nude Eyeshadow Palette](http://www.eyeslipsface.com/studio/eyes/eyeshadow/need_it_nude_eyeshadow_palette)
items.caption: Create an infinite number of subtly gorgeous daytime smoky eyes with this nude spectrum of shadows.
When it comes to power brows, who says you have to choose between a gel and a pencil? Pixi's two-in one Brow Duo offers the ease of a pencil and the staying power of a gel.
items.credit: Photo: Courtesy of Pixi by Petra

items.title: [Secret Mean Stinks Clear Gel Fearlessly Fresh](http://www.target.com/p/the-mean-stinks-collection/-/A-16124822)
items.caption: Stay fresh even after the most aggressive workout session or gym class with a quick swipe of Secret's Mean Stinks Gel Deodorant. This special formula shields you from all three different types of sweat: heat-induced, activity-induced, and stress-induced.

items.title: [Keratin Complex Smoothing Therapy Keratin Color Shampoo](http://www.drugstore.com/products/prod.asp?pid=362413&catid=183475&aid=338666&aparam=362413&kpid=362413&CAWELAID=120142990000089897&CAGPSPN=pla&kpid=362413)
items.caption: Keep newly colored strands — be it babylights or an all-over wash — vibrant with a gentle, yet fortifying conditioner like Keratin Complex Smoothing Therapy Keratin Color Shampoo.

items.title: [Yes to Tomatoes Acne Clearing Facial Toner](http://www.drugstore.com/products/prod.asp?pid=558432&catid=190119&aid=338666&aparam=558432&kpid=558432&CAWELAID=120142990000122866&CAGPSPN=pla&kpid=558432)
items.caption: Experts swear by the pore-shrinking abilities of witch hazel (a natural astringent). Tighten up in a flash — and treat acne — with a toner like Yes to Tomatoes Acne Clearing Facial Toner.
Liquid gold, bottled. This light argan oil boosts skin's brightness, toning for an all-over even glow.

items.title: [Garnier Full and Plush Ends Plumper](http://walmart.com/ip/41126929?wmlspartner=wlpa&selectedSellerId=0&adid=22222222227031048150&wl0=&wl1=g&wl2=c&wl3=53411942072&wl4=&wl5=pla&wl6=111814802432&veh=sem)
items.caption: End of summer have your ends completely fried? Plump up stringy-looking strands with Garnier's pomegranate-packed Ends Plumper.
An easy-to-use liquid liner? It does exist. Make your entrance with a cat eye, every single day of the week.

items.title: [Wet n Wild Color Icon Glitter Single In Distortion](http://www.walgreens.com/store/c/wet-n-wild-color-icon-glitter-single/ID=prod6206100-product)
items.caption: If glittery blue disco shadow is a bit much for the average day, we suggest incorporating it into your nighttime makeup moves. There's never been a better time to sing the blues.
items.credit: Photo: Courtesy of Wet n Wild

items.title: [Rimmel Keep Calm Lip Balm](http://www.walmart.com/ip/44374954?wmlspartner=wlpa&adid=22222222227033354159&wl0=&wl1=g&wl2=c&wl3=69080257472&wl4=&wl5=pla&wl6=135801581792&veh=sem)
items.caption: Lip balm is a locker essential, and how cute is this packaging?

items.title: [Avene Cleanance Expert Soin Emulsion](http://www.drugstore.com/products/prod.asp?pid=560487&catid=182258&aid=338666&aparam=560487&kpid=560487&CAWELAID=120142990000188507&CAGPSPN=pla&kpid=560487)
items.caption: Don't be fooled by its slim tube — Avene Cleanance Expert's three-in-one acne-fighting formula guarantees big results. A hydrating moisturizer, it also regulates the production of oil while mattifying skin and boosting luminosity.

items.title: [Revlon Photoready Eye Art Lid + Line + Lash](http://www.ulta.com/ulta/browse/productDetail.jsp?productId=xlsImpprod11851093)
items.caption: These sparkly, metallic shadow-and-liner duos are as fun as it gets. Take your school outfit to the next level with a colorful smoky eye. The possibilities are endless.

items.title: [TIGI Joyride Texturizing Powder Balm](http://www.ulta.com/ulta/browse/productDetail.jsp?productId=xlsImpprod12901013)
items.caption: Give limp strands an instant lift with a no-fuss texturizer that you can scrunch through wet or dry hair. We love Bed Head by TIGI Joyride Texturizing Powder Balm.

items.title: [Color Prevails Classic Lip Duo](http://www.drugstore.com/nonie-creme-colour-prevails-classic-lip-duo-lipstick-lip-gloss-06-orange-red/qxp544733)
items.caption: Two is definitely better than one, especially when it comes to lip service. We love this half-gloss, half-lipstick combo. Paint your pout with glittery gloss in the a.m., and then take it to the next level with a pigment punch once the final bell rings.

items.title: [Dippity Do Colorstick in Dark Glam](http://www.ulta.com/ulta/browse/productDetail.jsp?productId=xlsImpprod12891021)
items.caption: Go edgy — if only for a day — with a bold streak of deep berry or black in your hair. Dippity Do's Dark Glam Colorstick lets you play with your hair color, without the commitment — or a hefty price tag.
This intensely pigmented liquid lipstick stays on all. day. long. We swear. Trade in classic red for a darker statement lip come fall.

items.title: [Tresemme Make Waves Hi-Def Waves/Curls Shaping Gel Cream](http://www.drugstore.com/tresemme-expert-selection-make-waves-hi-def-wavescurls-shaping-gel-cream/qxp543792)
items.caption: Now that the sweltering heat of summer has died down (a bit), swap your frizz-fighter for a wave defining cream to soften crunchy curls. Try Tresemme Make Waves Hi-Def Waves/Curls Shaping Gel Cream.

items.title: [Sinful Colors Nail Polish in 24/7](https://shop.riteaid.com/sinful-colors-nail-enamel-24-7-920-0-5-fl-oz-15-ml-0430033?gdftrk=gdfV213277_a_7c4036_a_7c14908_a_7c0430033&gclid=Cj0KEQjwmNuuBRDTu5rDjr2kxJsBEiQAWlm6UjRfQv4r_DVvKEhcMGh5e2wJr5FFc25VSb7BfqucL1QaAvEN8P8HAQ&gclsrc=aw.ds)
items.caption: Bring summertime brights with you to class — on your nails. This neon pink keeps the beach party going all year long.

Plump up flat strands with an easy, in-shower bodifying treatment like John Frieda's 7-Day Volume Treatment. The formula penetrates every hair fiber on your head, thickening each strand for an overall fuller look. A bonus: it's safe even for color-treated hair.

items.title: [L'Oreal Paris Nutri-Gloss High Shine Glossing Mist](http://www.walmart.com/ip/L-Oreal-Paris-Advanced-Haircare-Nutri-Gloss-High-Shine-Glossing-Mist-3.4-oz/44910489)
items.caption: Nail the sleek-chic look with a shine-enhancing spray. If its name is any indication, L'Oreal Paris Nutri-Gloss High Shine Glossing Mist amplifies hair's natural sheen beyond belief.

fields.name: Emily Gaynor
fields.bio:
__What sort of advice would you give your 18-year-old self?__ 

I wish I would have known that everything works out in the end and if it didn’t, it most likely wasn’t meant to be. I stressed out over a lot of things—looking back I realize how big a waste of time that is. 

__What’s your favorite Teen Vogue moment?__ 

I have so many amazing *Teen Vogue* memories. I think my favorite was assisting on the Leighton Meester February 2009 cover shoot back when I was an intern. I was obsessed with Gossip Girl, and being on set in the LES with Leighton and Patrick Demachelier was definitely one the highlights of my entire college experience. At one point I had to stop pedestrians from walking into the shot and I remember thinking I’ve made it. Haha.

__Share a funny anecdote from a first job or internship.__ 

On my first day of my first internship, EVER, at *Teen Vogue* my purse hit the elevator alarm and the elevator stopped mid-ride—it was completely packed, too. I was mortified.  

__What beauty product are you loving right now?__

I can’t get enough of the Maybelline Master Kajal black liner. I love kohl-rimmed liner and this one is perfect. I also love that as it wears down you get an even more smudgy, smoky, rock ’n’ roll vibe. It’s basically the gift that keeps on giving. 

__What fashion item seems to always be on your shopping list?__ 

I can never have enough pairs of black jeans, but right now I’m in the market for overalls, culottes and a denim dress. 

__What’s your go-to karaoke song?__ 

"You Oughta Know” by Alanis Morissette, of course. 

__Who’s your favorite model and why?__ 

Well, it’s hard to pick, because I love models. But right now, I’m loving Cat McNeil. She’s confident, quirky and has amazing tattoos. 

__What’s your favorite Instagram to follow (other than Teen Vogue)?__ 

I follow a ton of models that I love, but right now my favorite Instagram is [@theacademynewyork](https://instagram.com/theacademynewyork/). They post really out-there images and quotes. And anything cat-related is always an instant-follow. 

__What’s your favorite meal?__ 

Tacos! All day, every day.
fields.title: Digital Beauty Editor

fields.name: Tina Ferraro
fields.bio:
__What sort of advice would you give your 18-year-old self?__ 

Read and write as much as you can, about anything and everything. Don’t give up on your dreams, and when (not if) they come true, don’t be afraid to dream bigger. And of course, go easy on the eyeshadow (I was a big fan of the daytime smoky eye in high school...).

__What’s your favorite *Teen Vogue* moment?__ 

Impromptu SnapChat photo shoots with Elaine Welteroth and Emily Gaynor trying on crazy-colored lipsticks.

__Share a funny anecdote from a first job or internship.__ 

During Best of Beauty testing at my internship at *Allure*, we laid out close to 100 different lipsticks sans caps for the beauty director to review. Can you guess how long it took to match all of the caps to their rightful owners?

__What beauty product are you loving right now?__ 

Dolce and Gabbana's new matte red lipsticks. I very rarely rock lip color, but the shades in this collection may convert me to a full-time lipstick-wearer.

__What fashion item seems to always be on your shopping list?__ 

I can’t ever resist a great pair of shoes—even when "window-shopping."

__What’s your favorite meal?__ 

Anything stuffed with cheese and over 500 calories.
